Put the tripe in a large stock pot. Add the vegetables and peppercorns and cover with water. Simmer for 4 hours.Fry the pancetta, carrot, onion, fennel and garlic in olive oil for 10 minutes. Add the chilli flakes, tomatoes and cooked tripe. Simmer for 10 minutes to thicken, then add the wine and continue to simmer for 30â€“40 minutes.Serve in bowls with the freshly chopped herbs and plenty of grated Parmesan.